scripts.comment: Let's create a custom block to average some numbers! Edit the block on the left to work on the problem!
Some example usages of the block can be found below!
A more advanced example is shown below. This example prompts the user for 5 messages. The positivity of these messages are then plotted and averaged!
What if we wanted to record the "moving average" or the average after each individual message, too? Could we add that line to the figure, too?

block.l: var myself = this; function getContext(canvas) { var context = canvas.getContext('2d'); context.font = size + 'px monospace' context.textAlign = 'left'; context.textBaseline = 'top'; context.fillStyle = myself.color.toString(); return context; } var canvas = newCanvas(new Point(1, 1), true); var ctx = getContext(canvas); var metrics = ctx.measureText(text); canvas.width = metrics.width; canvas.height = 2 * (metrics.actualBoundingBoxDescent + metrics.actualBoundingBoxAscent); ctx = getContext(canvas); ctx.fillText(text, 0, 0); return new Costume(canvas);
